title: Ju Wenjun Wins Women's World Rapid Chess Championship 2017 Without Losing a Single Game
description:

The "King Salman World Blitz & Rapid Championships 2017" in Riyadh from December 26th to 30th. The first five rounds of the rapid tournament take place on December 26th. A record $2 million prize fund has attracted most of the world's best players.

Tingjie Lei vs Ju Wenjun
World Rapid Championship (Women) (2017), Riyadh KSA, rd 4, Dec-26 
Four Knights Game: Spanish. Symmetrical Variation (C49)

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nc3 Nc6 4. Bb5 Bb4 5. O-O O-O 6. d3 d6 7. Bg5 Ne7 8. Ne2 c6 9. Ba4 Ng6 10. c3 Ba5 11. Ng3 h6 12. Be3 d5 13. ed5 Nd5 14. Bd2 Bb6 15. d4 Bg4 16. h3 Bf3 17. Qf3 ed4 18. c4 Nde7 19. Rfe1 Bc7 20. b4 Ne5 21. Qb3 Rb8 22. f4 b5 23. fe5 ba4 24. Qd3 Ng6 25. e6 Qd6 26. Nf1 Ne5 27. ef7 Rf7 28. Qe2 Qg6 29. Kh1 Nd3 30. g4 Ne1 31. Be1 d3 32. Qg2 Qf6
